To understand Valemont you should know that it was created as a series of 60-90 second episodes aired on MTV in the commercial break periods of other shows. Effectively, it is an early  "webisode" type show and what you can view here are compilations of those scenes into more conventional longform episodes. However, the incredible choppiness of constructing a story a minute and a half at a time has left an indelible mark weakening the show overall. Aside from the choppy pacing, the writing is nothing notable, nor is any of the acting. The tropes and concepts in the show - think of Hogwarts for Vampires and Potential Vampires Who Don't Know It - do not really feel fresh or well-executed. Is it horror? Urban Fantasy? Romance? It doesn't know itself. I did watch the whole series out of vague curiosity to see if they would actually go anywhere interesting and they really didn't. There were a few moments that were good but overall it's just the sort of thing you play in the background while reading a book.

Wow, this might have been good, but it wasn't. The concept was great, a university where vampires "change" and learn how to behave. The problem was that every character was a cardboard cutout cliche. The angry sister, the "dead" brother, the search for the truth, the "I'm not afraid!" idiocy of the main character. (Why is it that people who write stuff like this think it's a GOOD thing to be fearless?) The acting, when there was acting, was often overblown. (I expected Eric to twirl a mustache at one point.) And the sister? There was only one emotion she did well- anger. Anything else was just not believable.

Then there are the scripts. I feel for the writer(s). They had five episodes to try and get their characters set, their storyline moving and the audience interested. Obviously, they were rushed, and the result was more like a graphic novel, a bad graphic novel, than a television series. The phone video prop moved the story along, but it was contrived and clunky.

This show had potential but the script writing is "So Bad" ! So for the first 3 episodes there are writing flaws but still entertaining to keep my interest. The major flaws are as follows;

1. The story is rushed!! Meaning major character development never takes place to really capture your interest; so, the characters become superficial.
2. Each episode is about 18 -20 mins long. it's like watching a trailer to a movie.
3. Vampires in this show are as mortal and uninteresting as humans. They just age slower. Lame!!! What these writers don't seem to understand is that the most alluring thing about vampires is not that they drink blood to survive (that's just a limitation) BUT their immortality which these vamps don't have.
4. Cell phone / iPod mp3 player interludes are silly and they get annoying. I feel like I'm watching a video game when they cut to those scenes but without a XBox / PSP controller. LOL! - it's just stupid!!!

I get to episode 5: Main character drinks blood from her necklace pendant and she goes on some LSD trip that for some reason are events that are actually happening in the show (which is NOT consistent with the other vamp LSD type trips she goes on).

The writing is so bad that its just stupid, the acting gets worse because these actors have no background in which to pull from and by episode 5, it makes no sense at all.

For those GEN X: remember when MTV was really good 24/7 "Music"? I feel sorry for Millennials and Gen Y. This channel is technically "R"TV (for Reality crap)
